# Architecture plan for Issue #121: Remove message-card padding and reduce chat panel left padding

## Project/module structure
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` renders the unified chat feed and message list markup. No component or data-flow changes are needed for this issue.
- `frontend/src/styles.css` owns the Tailwind component-layer classes for the chat panel, chat list, and individual message cards. This is the only expected implementation surface.
- `shared/src/*`, `backend/src/*`, and database migrations remain out of scope because the issue is purely visual and does not affect message schemas, APIs, or persistence.

## Issue dependencies and sequencing
- This issue has no dependencies and can be implemented independently.
- The change should focus on the existing chat/feed styling introduced by earlier feed layout work, preserving existing rendering, polling, history loading, and accessibility behavior.

## Key design decisions
- Remove or minimize the inner padding on `.tlhn-chat-message` so message card content sits tighter within each card.
- Reduce only the left padding on `.tlhn-chat-panel` while keeping top/right/bottom spacing stable, e.g. `py-3 pr-3 pl-1`.
- Prefer a CSS-only adjustment in `frontend/src/styles.css`; avoid touching React markup unless visual validation shows a structural spacing source elsewhere.
- Keep TLHN branding, copy, message ordering, avatars, faction labels, and timestamps unchanged.
- Validate with the frontend/package build or lint command after implementation and inspect the chat panel at mobile/narrow widths where the requested padding reduction is most visible.
